---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ProjectCard from "../components/ProjectCard.astro";
---

<Layout title="Projects — Adam Richie-Halford" description="Selected projects and open-source work by Adam Richie-Halford.">
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-16">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono text-accent mb-4 tracking-wide">Projects</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-50 mb-6">
        Things I've built and shipped.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        A selection of technical projects spanning educational technology,
        scientific computing, and open-source infrastructure. For a full
        publication list, see my
        <a
          href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=Jy76il8AAAAJ"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light transition-colors"
        >Google Scholar</a> profile.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6">
      <div class="group relative rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-6 hover:border-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-900 transition-all duration-300">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">
            ROAR: Rapid Online Assessment of Reading
          </h3>

          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-200 mb-2">The Problem</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-400">
                Schools and researchers need reliable, scalable reading assessments that work across
                diverse devices, networks, and student populations, with strict privacy requirements
                and measurement validity constraints.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-200 mb-2">What I Own</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-400">
                Team of six engineers (and growing), technical roadmap, full-stack architecture,
                data pipeline design, production reliability, and cross-functional coordination
                with researchers, educators, and school districts.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-200 mb-2">Technical Choices</h4>
              <ul class="text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                <li>▸ Web-based assessment delivery (browser-native, no installs)</li>
                <li>▸ Real-time data pipelines for research analytics</li>
                <li>▸ FERPA-compliant student data handling</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-200 mb-2">Scale</h4>
              <ul class="text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                <li>▸ 309 districts, 2,708 schools rostered</li>
                <li>▸ 160,000+ users who have completed assessments</li>
                <li>▸ 873,000+ assessment runs</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1">
            <span class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-700">EdTech</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-700">Web Platform</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-700">Data Pipelines</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-700">Leadership</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-700">FERPA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 pt-2">
            <a
              href="https://roar.stanford.edu/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-sm font-medium text-accent hover:text-accent-light transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1"
            >
              Website
              <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 6H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 3 8.25v10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 5.25 21h10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 18 18.75V10.5m-10.5 6L21 3m0 0h-5.25M21 3v5.25" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ProjectCard
        title="pyAFQ: Automated Fiber Quantification"
        description="Open-source Python pipeline for automated tractography and white-matter analysis of diffusion MRI data."
        role="Core developer. Designed the analysis pipeline, implemented statistical methods, and built quality-controlled data resources."
        impact="Published in Nature Methods and Scientific Data. Used by neuroimaging labs worldwide."
        links={[
          { label: "Documentation", href: "https://yeatmanlab.github.io/pyAFQ/" },
          { label: "GitHub", href: "https://github.com/yeatmanlab/pyAFQ" },
          { label: "Nature Methods", href: "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-021-01185-5" },
        ]}
        tags={["Python", "Neuroimaging", "Open Source", "Data Science"]}
      />

      <ProjectCard
        title="Cloudknot"
        description="A Python library that lets researchers run existing code on AWS Batch with minimal configuration. Eliminates the boilerplate of containerization, IAM setup, and job queue management."
        role="Creator and maintainer. Designed the API, implemented AWS integrations, and published at SciPy 2018."
        impact="Enabled researchers without cloud expertise to scale computations to hundreds of parallel jobs."
        links={[
          { label: "Documentation", href: "https://nrdg.github.io/cloudknot/" },
          { label: "GitHub", href: "https://github.com/nrdg/cloudknot" },
          { label: "SciPy Paper", href: "http://conference.scipy.org/proceedings/scipy2018/adam_richie-halford.html" },
        ]}
        tags={["Python", "AWS", "Cloud Computing", "Open Source"]}
      />

      <ProjectCard
        title="Groupyr: Sparse Group Lasso"
        description="A scikit-learn-compatible Python library implementing the sparse group lasso for high-dimensional supervised learning with grouped features."
        role="Lead developer. Designed the API, implemented optimization algorithms, and published in JOSS."
        impact="Published in Journal of Open Source Software. Used for feature selection in neuroimaging studies (PLOS Computational Biology)."
        links={[
          { label: "GitHub", href: "https://github.com/richford/groupyr" },
          { label: "JOSS", href: "https://doi.org/10.21105/joss.03024" },
          { label: "PLOS CompBio", href: "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1009136" },
        ]}
        tags={["Python", "Machine Learning", "Statistics", "Open Source"]}
      />

      <ProjectCard
        title="AFQ-Browser"
        description="A browser-based tool for interactive visualization and analysis of diffusion MRI tractometry data."
        role="Core developer. Built interactive web visualizations for white-matter tract profiles."
        impact="Published in Nature Communications. Enabled collaborative, reproducible analysis of neuroimaging data."
        links={[
          { label: "GitHub", href: "https://github.com/yeatmanlab/AFQ-Browser" },
          { label: "Nature Comms", href: "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-018-03297-7" },
        ]}
        tags={["JavaScript", "Visualization", "Neuroimaging", "Open Source"]}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-slate-800/50 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-8">Selected Publications</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-8">
        Full list on
        <a
          href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=Jy76il8AAAAJ"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light transition-colors"
        >Google Scholar</a>
        or in my
        <a
          href="/cv.pdf"
          class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light transition-colors"
        >CV</a>.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-300">
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2022</span> &middot;
          <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, Cieslak M, Ai L, et al.
          An analysis-ready and quality controlled resource for pediatric brain white-matter research.
          <em>Scientific Data</em>.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41597-022-01695-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2021</span> &middot;
          Kruper J, Yeatman JD, <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, et al.
          Evaluating the reliability of human brain white matter tractometry.
          <em>Aperture Neuro</em>.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2021.02.24.432740" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2021</span> &middot;
          <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, Yeatman J, Simon N, Rokem A.
          Multidimensional analysis and detection of informative features in human brain white matter.
          <em>PLOS Computational Biology</em>.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1009136" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2021</span> &middot;
          Cieslak M, et al. (incl. <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>).
          QSIPrep: an integrative platform for preprocessing and reconstructing diffusion MRI data.
          <em>Nature Methods</em>.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-021-01185-5" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2020</span> &middot;
          <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, Drut J, Bulgac A.
          Emergence of a pseudogap in the BCS-BEC crossover.
          <em>Physical Review Letters</em>.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.125.060403" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2018</span> &middot;
          <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, Rokem A.
          Cloudknot: A Python Library to Run your Existing Code on AWS Batch.
          <em>SciPy 2018</em>.
          <a href="http://conference.scipy.org/proceedings/scipy2018/adam_richie-halford.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">paper</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-slate-400">2018</span> &middot;
          Yeatman JD, <strong class="text-slate-200">Richie-Halford A</strong>, Smith JK, Keshavan A, Rokem A.
          A browser-based tool for visualization and analysis of diffusion MRI data.
          <em>Nature Communications</em>.
          <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-018-03297-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">doi</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
